The paper discusses identifying crosscutting concerns in software systems, which is a common problem in software engineering (cs.SE). The paper specifically focuses on using aspect mining techniques, which are commonly used in programming languages (cs.PL) and software development (cs.SD). The paper also involves evaluating and comparing the results of these techniques, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
